        {
          "text": "<p>If you place a king in any of the <INSERTION_INDEX_1> corners, the other king will have <INSERTION_INDEX_2> spots to go and there are <INSERTION_INDEX_3> corners, so <INSERTION_INDEX_4>.If you place a king in any of the <INSERTION_INDEX_5> edges, the other king will have <INSERTION_INDEX_6> spots to go and there are <INSERTION_INDEX_7> edges so <INSERTION_INDEX_8>. That gives us <INSERTION_INDEX_9> spots for the other king to go into in total.So <INSERTION_INDEX_10> is the answer.~andliu766, captaindiamond868 (minor edits)~AliceDubbleYou</p>",
