          "text": "<p>We see that the center is not a viable spot for either of the kings to be in, as it would attack all nearby squares.</p><p>This gives three combinations: </p><p>Corner-corner: There are 4 corners, and none of them are touching orthogonally or diagonally, so it's <INSERTION_INDEX_1></p><p>Corner-edge: For each corner, there are two edges that don't border it, <INSERTION_INDEX_2></p><p>Edge-edge: The only possible combinations of this that work are top-bottom and left-right edges, so <INSERTION_INDEX_3> for this type</p><p><br/><INSERTION_INDEX_4></p><p>Multiply by two to account for arrangements of colors to get <INSERTION_INDEX_5> ~ c_double_sharp</p>",
